  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Hi all,\r\n\r\nCurrently, many tests in our services involve checking for logs being fired in goroutines. We can implement a function as part of the LogHandler in the `sharding/internal` package that waits for a log to be written by using channels and mutexes in order to make our testing situations easy and feasible.\r\n\r\nWe can do stuff like:\r\n\r\n```go\r\ngo doSomethingThatLogs()\r\nhandler.WaitForLog()\r\nhandler.VerifyLogMsg(\"yay this is the log\")\r\n```\r\n\r\nCurrently, we resort to using channels within goroutines that we can listen to in our tests and then verify log messages, but this subjects us to creating situations that block certain routines. We should find a way to implement WaitForLog without causing race conditions or deadlock.\r\n",
